# pyenv
#   For a library or app, you might want to share your .python-version.
#   Document it and uncomment if necessary.
# .python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in case of collaboration, if one uses a different OS than other team members,
#   dependency resolution might fail, so you can ignore Pipfile.lock
# Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, it is generally recommended to include poetry.lock in version control.
#   poetry.lock
#   Pedantic note: poetry.lock must be in version control for repeatable builds.

# pdm
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, it is generally recommended to include pdm.lock in version control.
# pdm.lock
#   pdm stores project-wide configurations in .pdm.toml
.pdm.toml
.pdm-python
.pdm-build/

